@shristijoshi @tirimiridai @ranju_darshana 2. Depending on the intensity of distress, you will want to escalate the intensity of your response:
- self-help/youtube resources etc/social connections
- short-term therapy
- long-term therapy
- short-term meds (e.g., for sleep)
- long-term meds (e.g., PTSD)
- hospital/rehab.

@shristijoshi @tirimiridai @ranju_darshana ...if you use online resources, look for reliable sources (mental health professionals, universities etc). @shristijoshi @tirimiridai @ranju_darshana Longer term: 
1. Build solidarity with people who understand you, work on your mental health and as you get ready, get involved in changing the conditions that distress you. Get therapy if you can....
